# Flutter / Dart Conventions

## Naming

- Files: snake_case (`user_profile.dart`)
- Classes: PascalCase (`UserProfile`)
- Variables/methods: camelCase (`getUserProfile`)
- Constants: camelCase with const (`const primaryColor`)
- Private members: _camelCase (`_hashedPin`)

## Widgets

- Screens end with `Screen` (HomeScreen, LockScreen)
- Reusable widgets end with their role (ProfileCard, PinInput)
- Extract any widget >50 lines into its own file
- Always provide a key parameter to stateful widgets

## Models

All models must have: a named constructor, `fromMap()` factory, `toMap()` method, and `copyWith()` method.

## Services

- All services must be a class with private constructor
- Database operations only in DatabaseService
- Platform channel calls only in AppLockService
- Auth logic only in AuthService

## Riverpod State Management

- StateNotifierProvider for complex state
- FutureProvider for async data fetching
- Provider for simple dependencies (services, repos)
- All providers defined in their feature folder
- Never use context.read() inside build() — use ref.watch()

## UI / UX — Material 3

- Use Material 3 (useMaterial3: true in ThemeData) for all UI
- Build themes with ColorScheme.fromSeed() — never manually pick individual component colors
- Use M3 components: FilledButton, OutlinedButton, SearchBar, NavigationBar, SegmentedButton, InputChip, etc.
- Use M3 typography via Theme.of(context).textTheme (displayLarge, titleMedium, bodySmall, etc.)
- Use M3 elevation and surface tint system — avoid manual BoxShadow for elevated surfaces
- Support light and dark mode via separate ColorScheme seeds
- Lock screen: clean, minimal — just PIN input and profile name, showing which partner's app is protected
- All screens must handle loading, error, and empty states
- Use smooth transitions between screens (MaterialPageRoute or page transitions API)
- Friendly design: warm colors, emoji support for profile avatars
